abstractText: Many techniques to assess egg-to-fry survival involve a multitude of sub-estimators that can confound any direct effects by compounding the variances of each individual sub-estimate. Therefore, a direct measurement from egg to pre-emergent or emergent fry stage is often a better estimator. In this case egg boxes are used to estimate egg incubation success.
title: Collection of Egg-to-Fry Incubation Boxes v1.0
